The '''Belgrade Circle''' is an [[NGO]] established in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]], in February 1992.
Initially, the organisation hosted lectures and discussions with mainly Serbian intellectuals, united by their opposition to the [[nationalist]] policies of [[Slobodan Milošević]]. The Belgrade Circle formed links with NGOs in other parts of the former Yugoslavia, and began to gain an international reputation, hosting lectures by internationally acclaimed intellectuals including [[Jacques Derrida]], [[Christopher Norris (critic)|Christopher Norris]] and [[Richard Rorty]].<ref>{{cite book|title=The Social Construction of Man, the State, and War: Identity, Conflict, and Violence in Former Yugoslavia|first=Franke|last=Wilmer|year=2002|location=London|publisher=Routledge|isbn=0415929636|page=222|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=TWo_sxMW-qIC&pg=PA222}}</ref> The organisation now focuses on strengthening [[civil society]], and works in co-operation with universities and academics from across the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.belgradecircle.org/eng/aboutus/belgradecircle.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929062417/http://www.belgradecircle.org/eng/aboutus/belgradecircle.pdf|dead-url=yes|archive-date=29 September 2007|title=Belgrade Circle NGO: A Brief History|publisher=Belgrade Circle|accessdate=9 November 2010}}</ref> It also publishes the ''Belgrade Circle Journal'', which is a member of the [[Eurozine]] network<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurozine.com/journals/belgradecircle/selfdescription.html|title=Belgrade Circle Journal self-description|publisher=Eurozine|accessdate=9 November 2010}}</ref> and has published prominent thinkers such as Rorty, [[Jürgen Habermas]] and [[Noam Chomsky]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Secor |first=Laura |date=September 1999 |title=Testaments Betrayed |url=http://linguafranca.mirror.theinfo.org/9909/testbet.html |magazine=[[Lingua Franca (magazine)|Lingua Franca]]|access-date=19 June 2018 }}</ref>
