{{Infobox book | name = Darcy's Story | image = darcy story cover.gif | image_size = 200px | caption = First edition cover | author = Janet Aylmer | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = England | language = English | series = | subject = | genre = | publisher = Copperfield Books | pub_date = | english_pub_date = 1 July 1996 | media_type = Paperback | pages = 240 | isbn = 978-0-9528210-2-1 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Darcy's Story''''' by Janet Aylmer was one of the first novels published after the success of the [[BBC One]] serial of [[Jane Austen]]'s ''[[Pride and Prejudice (1995 TV series)|Pride and Prejudice]]'' in 1995.
Published in England in 1996, the novel tells the story from [[Mr. Darcy]]'s point of view. In 2006, the novel was published by [[HarperCollins]] in the US. According to the author's website, over 150,000 copies of this book have been sold worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.janetaylmer.com/|title=Home Page|website=www.janetaylmer.com|access-date=2016-04-02}}</ref>
Author Janet Aylmer has since published a sequel, ''Dialogue with Darcy''.<ref>[http://www.janetaylmer.com/dialogue.html ''Dialogue with Darcy''] at JanetAylmer.com</ref>
In all, Aylmer has written five novels and one non-fiction book about history in [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]] linked with Jane Austen:
