{{Icelandic name|Halla Signý}}
{{Infobox Politician|name=Halla Signý Kristjánsdóttir|image=[[File:Halla Signý.jpg|200px]]|office=|president=|primeminister=|predecessor=|successor=|term_start=|term_end=|office2=|term_start2=|term_end2=|predecessor2=|successor2=|birth_date={{birth date and age|1964|5|1|df=y}}|birth_place=[[Flateyri]], [[Iceland]]|parents=Kristján Guðmundsson (1918-1988)<br>Árilía Jóhannesdóttir (1923-2014)|spouse=Sigurður G. Sverrisson|children=|alma_mater=[[Bifröst University]] ([[B.S.]])|profession=|party=[[Progressive Party (Iceland)|Progressive Party]]}}

'''Halla Signý Kristjánsdóttir''' (born 1 May 1964) is an [[Iceland|Icelandic]] politician who is a member of the [[Althing]] (Iceland's parliament) for the Northwest Constituency since 2017<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kjarninn.is/staflar/kosningar/2017-10-28-thessi-nadu-kjori-i-althingiskosningunum/|title=Þessi náðu kjöri í Alþingiskosningunum|date=2017-10-29|work=Kjarninn|access-date=2018-04-06|language=is-IS}}</ref>.

