{{Infobox Central bank |bank_name_in_local = Banca Naţională a Moldovei <small>{{ro icon}}</small> |image_1 = |image_title_1 = |image_2 = |image_title_2 = |image_width_2 = |headquarters = [[Chişinău]] |established = 1991 |president = [[Sergiu Cioclea]] |leader_title = Governor |bank_of = [[Republic of Moldova|Moldova]] |currency = [[Moldovan leu]] |currency_iso = MDL |reserves = |borrowing_rate = |deposit_rate = |website = [http://www.bnm.md/ www.bnm.md] |preceded = |succeeded = |footnotes = }}
The '''National Bank of Moldova''' ({{lang-ro|Banca Naţională a Moldovei}}) is the [[central bank]] of the [[Republic of Moldova]].
The National Bank of Moldova is a [[legal]], [[Public company|public]], [[Autonomous entity|autonomous]] person responsible to the [[Parliament of Moldova|Parliament]]. The main objective of the NBM is the achievement and maintenance of the stability of the national currency. The National Bank cooperates with the [[Government of Moldova|Government]] with the view to achieving its objectives and, according to the [[Law]], undertakes the necessary measures to implement such cooperation. The NBM periodically informs the public about [[macroeconomic]] analysis, [[financial market]] evolution and [[statistic]] data, including on [[money supply]], [[Credit (finance)|credit]] granting, [[balance of payments]] and [[foreign exchange market]].
==History== [[Leonid Tălmaci]] served as the first Governor of the National Bank (1991–2009). [[Dorin Drăguțanu]] has served as the Governor of the National Bank since November 2009.<ref>[http://eleonora-lisnic.blogspot.com/2009/11/dorin-dragutanu-guvernator-al-bnm.html ''Dorin Drăguţanu, guvernator al BNM''] besøkt 30. november 2011. ([https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=ru&tl=no&js=n&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=2&eotf=1&u=http%3A%2F%2Feleonora-lisnic.blogspot.com%2F2009%2F11%2Fdorin-dragutanu-guvernator-al-bnm.html Oversatt artikkel, Google Translate])</ref> On the 11th of March 2016, Sergiu Cioclea was elected as the new Governor by the country's parliament. ==See also== *[[Economy of Moldova]] *[[Moldovan leu]]
