{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Wilfred Owen: A Remembrance Tale | image = | caption = | show_name_2 = | genre = [[Documentary]] | creator = | developer = | writer = | director = [[Louise Hooper]] | creative_director = | presenter = [[Jeremy Paxman]] | starring = | judges = | voices = | narrated = | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | composer = | country = United Kingdom | language = English | num_seasons = <!-- or num_series --> | num_episodes = 1 | list_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = | editor = | location = | cinematography = | company = [[Modern Television]] | camera = | runtime = 59 minutes | distributor = | channel = [[BBC One]] | picture_format = | audio_format = | first_run = | first_aired = 11 November 2007 | last_aired = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | related = | website = | production_website = }}
'''''Wilfred Owen: A Remembrance Tale''''' was a 1-hour 2007 BBC documentary on the life of the [[First World War]] poet [[Wilfred Owen]]. It was presented by [[Jeremy Paxman]] and starred [[Samuel Barnett (actor)|Samuel Barnett]] as Owen and [[Deborah Findlay]] as his mother Susan. It premiered on [[BBC One]] on [[Remembrance Sunday]] 2007.
